    "title": "Senior Plant Manager at Colgate-Palmolive India Capital India",
    "description": "We at Colgate-Palmolive India Capital India are looking for an experienced Plant Manager based out of Delhi. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Colgate-Palmolive India Capital India:\nColgate-Palmolive India Capital India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Implement lean manufacturing and continuous improvement initiatives\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n• Monitor equipment performance and coordinate preventive maintenance\n• Ensure environmental compliance and waste management\n• Implement 5S, Kaizen, and Six Sigma practices on the shop floor\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in Lean Manufacturing\n• Proficiency in AutoCAD\n• Proficiency in SAP MM/PP\n• Proficiency in PPAP\n• Proficiency in TPM\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Learning & development budget\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Delhi, Delhi, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Colgate-Palmolive India Capital India!",
